ciscoIscsiModule.name: ciscoIscsiModule

revisions.description: Initial revision published of this MIB module.

CIscsiTransportProtocols.name: CIscsiTransportProtocols
CIscsiTransportProtocols.description: This data type is used to define the transport protocols that will carry iSCSI PDUs.
CIscsiTransportProtocols.reference: RFC791, RFC1700 The presently known, officially delegated numbers can be found at: http://www.iana.org/assignments/protocol-numbers

CIscsiDigestMethod.name: CIscsiDigestMethod
CIscsiDigestMethod.description: This data type represents the methods possible for digest negotiation. none - a placeholder for a secondary digest method that means only the primary method can be used. other - a digest method other than those defined below; noDigest - does not support digests (will operate without a digest (NOTE: implementations MUST support digests to be compliant with the iSCSI RFC); CRC32c - require a CRC32C digest.

cIscsiHdrIntegrityNone.name: cIscsiHdrIntegrityNone
cIscsiHdrIntegrityNone.description: The authoritative identifier when no integrity scheme (for either the header or data) is being used.

cIscsiHdrIntegrityCrc32c.name: cIscsiHdrIntegrityCrc32c
cIscsiHdrIntegrityCrc32c.description: The authoritative identifier when the integrity scheme (for either the header or data) is CRC-32c.

cIscsiDataIntegrityNone.name: cIscsiDataIntegrityNone
cIscsiDataIntegrityNone.description: The authoritative identifier when no integrity scheme (for either the header or data) is being used.

cIscsiDataIntegrityCrc32c.name: cIscsiDataIntegrityCrc32c
cIscsiDataIntegrityCrc32c.description: The authoritative identifier when the integrity scheme (for either the header or data) is CRC-32c.

cIscsiInstanceAttributesTable.name: cIscsiInstanceAttributesTable
cIscsiInstanceAttributesTable.description: A list of iSCSI instances present on the system.

cIscsiInstanceAttributesEntry.name: cIscsiInstanceAttributesEntry
cIscsiInstanceAttributesEntry.description: An entry (row) containing management information applicable to a particular iSCSI instance.

cIscsiInstIndex.name: cIscsiInstIndex
cIscsiInstIndex.description: An arbitrary integer used to uniquely identify a particular ISCSI instance.

cIscsiInstDescr.name: cIscsiInstDescr
cIscsiInstDescr.description: An octet string, determined by the implementation to describe the iSCSI instance. When only a single instance is present, this object may be set to the zero-length string; with multiple iSCSI instances, it may be used in an implementation-dependent manner to describe the purpose of the respective instance.

cIscsiInstVersionMin.name: cIscsiInstVersionMin
cIscsiInstVersionMin.description: Minimum version number of the iSCSI specification supported by this instance.

cIscsiInstVersionMax.name: cIscsiInstVersionMax
cIscsiInstVersionMax.description: Maximum version number of the iSCSI specification supported by this instance.

cIscsiInstVendorID.name: cIscsiInstVendorID
cIscsiInstVendorID.description: An octet string describing the manufacturer of the implementation of this instance.

cIscsiInstVendorVersion.name: cIscsiInstVendorVersion
cIscsiInstVendorVersion.description: An octet string set by the manufacturer describing the version of the implementation of this instance. The format of this string is determined solely by the manufacturer, and is for informational purposes only. It is unrelated to the iSCSI specification version numbers.

cIscsiInstPortalNumber.name: cIscsiInstPortalNumber
cIscsiInstPortalNumber.description: The number of rows in the cIscsiPortalAttributesTable which are currently associated with this iSCSI instance.

cIscsiInstNodeNumber.name: cIscsiInstNodeNumber
cIscsiInstNodeNumber.description: The number of rows in the cIscsiNodeAttributesTable which are currently associated with this iSCSI instance.

cIscsiInstSessionNumber.name: cIscsiInstSessionNumber
cIscsiInstSessionNumber.description: The number of rows in the cIscsiSessionAttributesTable which are currently associated with this iSCSI instance.

cIscsiInstSsnFailures.name: cIscsiInstSsnFailures
cIscsiInstSsnFailures.description: This object counts the number of times a session belonging to this instance has been failed.

cIscsiInstLastSsnFailureType.name: cIscsiInstLastSsnFailureType
cIscsiInstLastSsnFailureType.description: The counter object in the cIscsiInstSsnErrorStatsTable that was incremented when the last session failure occurred. If the reason for failure is not found in the cIscsiInstSsnErrorStatsTable, the value { 0.0 } is used instead.

cIscsiInstLastSsnRmtNodeName.name: cIscsiInstLastSsnRmtNodeName
cIscsiInstLastSsnRmtNodeName.description: An octet string describing the name of the remote node from the failed session.

cIscsiInstanceSsnErrorStatsTable.name: cIscsiInstanceSsnErrorStatsTable
cIscsiInstanceSsnErrorStatsTable.description: A list of error types that will cause a session failure.

cIscsiInstanceSsnErrorStatsEntry.name: cIscsiInstanceSsnErrorStatsEntry
cIscsiInstanceSsnErrorStatsEntry.description: An entry (row) containing management information applicable to a particular iSCSI instance.

cIscsiInstSsnDigestErrors.name: cIscsiInstSsnDigestErrors
cIscsiInstSsnDigestErrors.description: The count of sessions which were failed due to receipt of a PDU containing header or data digest errors.

cIscsiInstSsnCxnTimeoutErrors.name: cIscsiInstSsnCxnTimeoutErrors
cIscsiInstSsnCxnTimeoutErrors.description: The count of sessions which were failed due to a sequence exceeding a time limit.

cIscsiInstSsnFormatErrors.name: cIscsiInstSsnFormatErrors
cIscsiInstSsnFormatErrors.description: The count of sessions which were failed due to receipt of a PDU which contained a format error.

cIscsiPortalAttributesTable.name: cIscsiPortalAttributesTable
cIscsiPortalAttributesTable.description: A list of transport endpoints (using TCP or another transport protocol) used by this iSCSI instance. An iSCSI instance may use a portal to listen for incoming connections to its targets, to initiate connections to other targets, or both.

cIscsiPortalAttributesEntry.name: cIscsiPortalAttributesEntry
cIscsiPortalAttributesEntry.description: An entry (row) containing management information applicable to a particular portal instance.

cIscsiPortalIndex.name: cIscsiPortalIndex
cIscsiPortalIndex.description: An arbitrary integer used to uniquely identify a particular transport endpoint within this iSCSI instance.

cIscsiPortalRoles.name: cIscsiPortalRoles
cIscsiPortalRoles.description: A portal can operate in one or both of two roles: as a target portal and/or an initiator portal. When a new cIscsiPortalAttributesEntry is to be created, the agent should use this object as a hint for the creation of a new cIscsiTgtPortalAttributesEntry and/or cIscsiIntrPortalAttributesEntry.

cIscsiPortalAddrType.name: cIscsiPortalAddrType
cIscsiPortalAddrType.description: The type of Internet Network Address in the cIscsiPortalAddr.

cIscsiPortalMaxRecvDataSegLength.name: cIscsiPortalMaxRecvDataSegLength
cIscsiPortalMaxRecvDataSegLength.description: The maximum PDU length this portal can receive. This may be constrained by hardware characteristics and individual implementations may chose not to allow this object to be changed.

cIscsiPortalPrimaryHdrDigest.name: cIscsiPortalPrimaryHdrDigest
cIscsiPortalPrimaryHdrDigest.description: The preferred header digest for this portal.

cIscsiPortalPrimaryDataDigest.name: cIscsiPortalPrimaryDataDigest
cIscsiPortalPrimaryDataDigest.description: The preferred data digest method for this portal.

cIscsiPortalSecondaryHdrDigest.name: cIscsiPortalSecondaryHdrDigest
cIscsiPortalSecondaryHdrDigest.description: An alternate header digest preference for this portal.

cIscsiPortalSecondaryDataDigest.name: cIscsiPortalSecondaryDataDigest
cIscsiPortalSecondaryDataDigest.description: An alternate data digest preference for this portal.

cIscsiPortalRecvMarker.name: cIscsiPortalRecvMarker
cIscsiPortalRecvMarker.description: This object indicates whether or not this portal will request markers in it's incoming data stream.

cIscsiTgtPortalAttributesTable.name: cIscsiTgtPortalAttributesTable
cIscsiTgtPortalAttributesTable.description: A list of transport endpoints (using TCP or another transport protocol) on which this iSCSI instance listens for incoming connections to its targets.

cIscsiTgtPortalAttributesEntry.name: cIscsiTgtPortalAttributesEntry
cIscsiTgtPortalAttributesEntry.description: An entry (row) containing management information applicable to a particular portal instance that is used to listen for incoming connections to local targets. This row is populated for each cIscsiPortalAttributesEntry row that may be used as a target portal.

cIscsiTgtPortalPort.name: cIscsiTgtPortalPort
cIscsiTgtPortalPort.description: The portal's transport protocol port number on which the portal listens for incoming iSCSI connections when the portal is used as a target portal.

cIscsiTgtPortalTag.name: cIscsiTgtPortalTag
cIscsiTgtPortalTag.description: The portal's aggregation tag when portal is used as a target portal. Multiple-connection sessions may be aggregated over portals sharing an identical aggregation tag.

cIscsiIntrPortalAttributesTable.name: cIscsiIntrPortalAttributesTable
cIscsiIntrPortalAttributesTable.description: A list of Internet Network Addresses (using TCP or another transport protocol) from which this iSCSI instance may initiate connections to other targets.

cIscsiIntrPortalAttributesEntry.name: cIscsiIntrPortalAttributesEntry
cIscsiIntrPortalAttributesEntry.description: An entry (row) containing management information applicable to a particular portal instance that is used to initiate connections to iSCSI targets. This row is populated for each cIscsiPortalAttributesEntry row that may be used as an initiator portal.

cIscsiIntrPortalTag.name: cIscsiIntrPortalTag
cIscsiIntrPortalTag.description: The portal's aggregation tag when the portal is used as an initiator portal. Multiple-connection sessions may be aggregated over portals sharing an identical aggregation tag.

cIscsiNodeAttributesTable.name: cIscsiNodeAttributesTable
cIscsiNodeAttributesTable.description: A list of iSCSI nodes belonging to each iSCSI instance present on the local system. An iSCSI node can act as an initiator, a target, or both.

cIscsiNodeAttributesEntry.name: cIscsiNodeAttributesEntry
cIscsiNodeAttributesEntry.description: An entry (row) containing management information applicable to a particular iSCSI node.

cIscsiNodeIndex.name: cIscsiNodeIndex
cIscsiNodeIndex.description: An arbitrary integer used to uniquely identify a particular node within an iSCSI instance present on the local system.

cIscsiNodeName.name: cIscsiNodeName
cIscsiNodeName.description: A character string that is a globally unique identifier for this iSCSI node. The node name is independent of the location of the node, and can be resolved into a set of addresses through various discovery services.

cIscsiNodeAlias.name: cIscsiNodeAlias
cIscsiNodeAlias.description: A character string that is a human-readable name or description of the iSCSI node. If configured, this alias may be communicated to the initiator or target node at the remote end of the connection during a Login Request or Response message. This string is not used as an identifier, but can be displayed by the system's user interface in a list of initiators and/or targets to which it is connected. If no alias is configured, this object is a zero-length string.

cIscsiNodeRoles.name: cIscsiNodeRoles
cIscsiNodeRoles.description: A node can operate as in one or both of two roles: a target role and/or an initiator role.

cIscsiNodeTransportType.name: cIscsiNodeTransportType
cIscsiNodeTransportType.description: A pointer to the corresponding scsiTrnspt object in the CISCO-SCSI-MIB (which in turn points to this iSCSI node) allowing management stations to locate the SCSI-level Device that is represented by this cIscsiNode.

cIscsiNodeInitialR2T.name: cIscsiNodeInitialR2T
cIscsiNodeInitialR2T.description: This object indicates InitialR2T preference for this node - True = YES, False = will try to negotiate NO, will accept YES

cIscsiNodeBidiInitialR2T.name: cIscsiNodeBidiInitialR2T
cIscsiNodeBidiInitialR2T.description: This object indicates BidiInitialR2T preference for this node- True = YES, False = will try to negotiate NO, will accept YES

cIscsiNodeImmediateData.name: cIscsiNodeImmediateData
cIscsiNodeImmediateData.description: This object indicates ImmediateData preference for this node True = YES (but will accept NO), False = NO

cIscsiNodeMaxOutstandingR2T.name: cIscsiNodeMaxOutstandingR2T
cIscsiNodeMaxOutstandingR2T.description: Maximum number of outstanding R2Ts allowed per task.

cIscsiNodeFirstBurstSize.name: cIscsiNodeFirstBurstSize
cIscsiNodeFirstBurstSize.description: The maximum length (bytes) supported for unsolicited data to/from this node.

cIscsiNodeMaxBurstSize.name: cIscsiNodeMaxBurstSize
cIscsiNodeMaxBurstSize.description: The maximum number of bytes which can be sent within a single sequence of Data-In or Data-Out PDUs.

cIscsiNodeMaxConnections.name: cIscsiNodeMaxConnections
cIscsiNodeMaxConnections.description: The maximum number of connections allowed in each session to and/or from this node.

cIscsiNodeDataSequenceInOrder.name: cIscsiNodeDataSequenceInOrder
cIscsiNodeDataSequenceInOrder.description: The DataSequenceInOrder preference of this node. False (=No) indicates that iSCSI data PDU sequences may be transferred in any order. True (=Yes) indicates that data PDU sequences must be transferred using continuously increasing offsets, except during error recovery.

cIscsiNodeDataPduInOrder.name: cIscsiNodeDataPduInOrder
cIscsiNodeDataPduInOrder.description: The DataPDUInOrder preference of this node. False (=No) indicates that iSCSI data PDUs within sequences may be in any order. True (=Yes) indicates that data PDUs within sequences must be at continuously increasing addresses, with no gaps or overlay between PDUs.

cIscsiNodeDefaultTime2Wait.name: cIscsiNodeDefaultTime2Wait
cIscsiNodeDefaultTime2Wait.description: The DefaultTime2Wait preference of this node. This is the minimum time, in seconds, to wait before attempting an explicit/implicit logout or active task reassignment after an unexpected connection termination or a connection reset.

cIscsiNodeDefaultTime2Retain.name: cIscsiNodeDefaultTime2Retain
cIscsiNodeDefaultTime2Retain.description: The DefaultTime2Retain preference of this node. This is the maximum time, in seconds after an initial wait (Time2Wait), before which an active task reassignment is still possible after an unexpected connection termination or a connection reset.

cIscsiNodeErrorRecoveryLevel.name: cIscsiNodeErrorRecoveryLevel
cIscsiNodeErrorRecoveryLevel.description: The ErrorRecoveryLevel preference of this node. Currently, only 0-2 are valid. This object is designed to accommodate future error recover levels. Higher error recovery levels imply support in addition to support for the lower error level functions. In otherwords, error level 2 implies support for levels 0-1, since those functions are subsets of error level 2.

cIscsiTargetAttributesTable.name: cIscsiTargetAttributesTable
cIscsiTargetAttributesTable.description: An entry (row) containing management information applicable to a particular node that can take on a target role.

cIscsiTargetAttributesEntry.name: cIscsiTargetAttributesEntry
cIscsiTargetAttributesEntry.description: An entry (row) containing management information applicable to a particular target.

cIscsiTgtLoginFailures.name: cIscsiTgtLoginFailures
cIscsiTgtLoginFailures.description: This object counts the number of times a login attempt to this local target has failed.

cIscsiTgtLastFailureTime.name: cIscsiTgtLastFailureTime
cIscsiTgtLastFailureTime.description: The timestamp of the most recent failure of a login attempt to this target. A value of zero indicates that no such failures have occurred.

cIscsiTgtLastFailureType.name: cIscsiTgtLastFailureType
cIscsiTgtLastFailureType.description: The type of the most recent failure of a login attempt to this target, represented as the OID of the counter object in cIscsiTargetLoginStatsTable for which the relevant instance was incremented. A value of 0.0 indicates a type which is not represented by any of the counters in cIscsiTargetLoginStatsTable.

cIscsiTgtLastIntrFailureName.name: cIscsiTgtLastIntrFailureName
cIscsiTgtLastIntrFailureName.description: An octet string giving the name of the initiator that failed the last login attempt.

cIscsiTgtLastIntrFailureAddrType.name: cIscsiTgtLastIntrFailureAddrType
cIscsiTgtLastIntrFailureAddrType.description: The type of Internet Network Address in cIscsiTgtLastIntrFailureAddr.

cIscsiTgtLastIntrFailureAddr.name: cIscsiTgtLastIntrFailureAddr
cIscsiTgtLastIntrFailureAddr.description: An Internet Network Address giving the host address of the initiator that failed the last login attempt.

cIscsiTargetLoginStatsTable.name: cIscsiTargetLoginStatsTable
cIscsiTargetLoginStatsTable.description: A table of counters which keep a record of the results of initiators' login attempts to this target.

cIscsiTargetLoginStatsEntry.name: cIscsiTargetLoginStatsEntry
cIscsiTargetLoginStatsEntry.description: An entry (row) containing counters for each result of a login attempt to this target.

cIscsiTgtLoginAccepts.name: cIscsiTgtLoginAccepts
cIscsiTgtLoginAccepts.description: The count of Login Response PDUs with status 0x0000, Accept Login, transmitted by this target.

cIscsiTgtLoginOtherFails.name: cIscsiTgtLoginOtherFails
cIscsiTgtLoginOtherFails.description: The number of Login Response PDUs which were transmitted by this target, and which were not counted by any other object in the row.

cIscsiTgtLoginRedirects.name: cIscsiTgtLoginRedirects
cIscsiTgtLoginRedirects.description: The count of Login Response PDUs with status class 0x01, Redirection, transmitted by this target.

cIscsiTgtLoginAuthorizeFails.name: cIscsiTgtLoginAuthorizeFails
cIscsiTgtLoginAuthorizeFails.description: The count of Login Response PDUs with status 0x0202, Forbidden Target, transmitted by this target. If this counter is incremented, an cIscsiTgtLoginFailure notification should be generated.

cIscsiTgtLoginAuthenticateFails.name: cIscsiTgtLoginAuthenticateFails
cIscsiTgtLoginAuthenticateFails.description: The count of Login Response PDUs with status 0x0201, Authentication Failed, transmitted by this target If this counter is incremented, an cIscsiTgtLoginFailure notification should be generated.

cIscsiTgtLoginNegotiateFails.name: cIscsiTgtLoginNegotiateFails
cIscsiTgtLoginNegotiateFails.description: The number of times a target has effectively refused a login because the parameter negotiation failed. [Ed. While this situation can occur, the exact mechanism is as yet undefined in the iSCSI Protocol Spec.] If this counter is incremented, an cIscsiTgtLoginFailure notification should be generated.

cIscsiTargetLogoutStatsTable.name: cIscsiTargetLogoutStatsTable
cIscsiTargetLogoutStatsTable.description: When a target receives a Logout command, it responds with a Logout Response that carries a status code. This table contains counters for both normal and abnormal logout requests received by this target.

cIscsiTargetLogoutStatsEntry.name: cIscsiTargetLogoutStatsEntry
cIscsiTargetLogoutStatsEntry.description: An entry (row) containing counters of Logout Response PDUs that were received by this target.

cIscsiTgtLogoutNormals.name: cIscsiTgtLogoutNormals
cIscsiTgtLogoutNormals.description: The count of Logout Command PDUs received by this target, with reason code 0 (closes the session).

cIscsiTgtLogoutOthers.name: cIscsiTgtLogoutOthers
cIscsiTgtLogoutOthers.description: The count of Logout Command PDUs received by this target, with any status code other than 0.

cIscsiTgtAuthAttributesTable.name: cIscsiTgtAuthAttributesTable
cIscsiTgtAuthAttributesTable.description: A list of initiator identities that are authorized to access each target node within each iSCSI instance present on the local system.

cIscsiTgtAuthAttributesEntry.name: cIscsiTgtAuthAttributesEntry
cIscsiTgtAuthAttributesEntry.description: An entry (row) containing management information applicable to a particular target node's authorized initiator identity.

cIscsiTgtAuthIndex.name: cIscsiTgtAuthIndex
cIscsiTgtAuthIndex.description: An arbitrary integer used to uniquely identify a particular target's authorized initiator identity within an iSCSI instance present on the local system.

cIscsiTgtAuthIdentity.name: cIscsiTgtAuthIdentity
cIscsiTgtAuthIdentity.description: A pointer to the corresponding IPS-AUTH MIB user entry that will be allowed to access this iSCSI target.

cIscsiInitiatorAttributesTable.name: cIscsiInitiatorAttributesTable
cIscsiInitiatorAttributesTable.description: A list of iSCSI nodes that can take on an initiator role, belonging to each iSCSI instance present on the local system.

cIscsiInitiatorAttributesEntry.name: cIscsiInitiatorAttributesEntry
cIscsiInitiatorAttributesEntry.description: An entry (row) containing management information applicable to a particular iSCSI node that has initiator capabilities.

cIscsiIntrLoginFailures.name: cIscsiIntrLoginFailures
cIscsiIntrLoginFailures.description: This object counts the number of times a login attempt from this local initiator has failed.

cIscsiIntrLastFailureTime.name: cIscsiIntrLastFailureTime
cIscsiIntrLastFailureTime.description: The timestamp of the most recent failure of a login attempt from this initiator. A value of zero indicates that no such failures have occurred.

cIscsiIntrLastFailureType.name: cIscsiIntrLastFailureType
cIscsiIntrLastFailureType.description: The type of the most recent failure of a login attempt from this initiator, represented as the OID of the counter object in cIscsiInitiatorLoginStatsTable for which the relevant instance was incremented. A value of 0.0 indicates a type which is not represented by any of the counters in cIscsiInitiatorLoginStatsTable.

cIscsiIntrLastTgtFailureName.name: cIscsiIntrLastTgtFailureName
cIscsiIntrLastTgtFailureName.description: An octet string giving the name of the target that failed the last login attempt.

cIscsiIntrLastTgtFailureAddrType.name: cIscsiIntrLastTgtFailureAddrType
cIscsiIntrLastTgtFailureAddrType.description: The type of Internet Network Address in cIscsiIntrLastTgtFailureAddr.

cIscsiIntrLastTgtFailureAddr.name: cIscsiIntrLastTgtFailureAddr
cIscsiIntrLastTgtFailureAddr.description: An Internet Network Address giving the host address of the target that failed the last login attempt.

cIscsiInitiatorLoginStatsTable.name: cIscsiInitiatorLoginStatsTable
cIscsiInitiatorLoginStatsTable.description: A table of counters which keep track of the results of this initiator's login attempts.

cIscsiInitiatorLoginStatsEntry.name: cIscsiInitiatorLoginStatsEntry
cIscsiInitiatorLoginStatsEntry.description: An entry (row) containing counters of each result of this initiator's login attempts.

cIscsiIntrLoginAcceptRsps.name: cIscsiIntrLoginAcceptRsps
cIscsiIntrLoginAcceptRsps.description: The count of Login Response PDUs with status 0x0000, Accept Login, received by this initiator.

cIscsiIntrLoginOtherFailRsps.name: cIscsiIntrLoginOtherFailRsps
cIscsiIntrLoginOtherFailRsps.description: The count of Login Response PDUs received by this initiator with any status code not counted in the objects below.

cIscsiIntrLoginRedirectRsps.name: cIscsiIntrLoginRedirectRsps
cIscsiIntrLoginRedirectRsps.description: The count of Login Response PDUs with status class 0x01, Redirection, received by this initiator.

cIscsiIntrLoginAuthFailRsps.name: cIscsiIntrLoginAuthFailRsps
cIscsiIntrLoginAuthFailRsps.description: The count of Login Response PDUs with status class 0x201, Authentication Failed, received by this initiator.

cIscsiIntrLoginAuthenticateFails.name: cIscsiIntrLoginAuthenticateFails
cIscsiIntrLoginAuthenticateFails.description: The number of times the initiator has aborted a login because the target could not be authenticated. No response is generated. If this counter is incremented, an cIscsiIntrLoginFailure notification should be generated.

cIscsiIntrLoginNegotiateFails.name: cIscsiIntrLoginNegotiateFails
cIscsiIntrLoginNegotiateFails.description: The number of times the initiator has aborted a login because parameter negotiation with the target failed. No response is generated. If this counter is incremented, an cIscsiIntrLoginFailure notification should be generated.

cIscsiInitiatorLogoutStatsTable.name: cIscsiInitiatorLogoutStatsTable
cIscsiInitiatorLogoutStatsTable.description: When an initiator attempts send a Logout command, the target responds with a Logout Response that carries a status code. This table contains a list of counters of Logout Response PDUs of each status code, that were received by each initiator belonging to this iSCSI instance present on this system.

cIscsiInitiatorLogoutStatsEntry.name: cIscsiInitiatorLogoutStatsEntry
cIscsiInitiatorLogoutStatsEntry.description: An entry (row) containing counters of Logout Response PDUs of each status code, that were generated by this initiator.

cIscsiIntrLogoutNormals.name: cIscsiIntrLogoutNormals
cIscsiIntrLogoutNormals.description: The count of Logout Command PDUs generated by this initiator with reason code 0 (closes the session).

cIscsiIntrLogoutOthers.name: cIscsiIntrLogoutOthers
cIscsiIntrLogoutOthers.description: The count of Logout Command PDUs generated by this initiator with any status code other than 0.

cIscsiIntrAuthAttributesTable.name: cIscsiIntrAuthAttributesTable
cIscsiIntrAuthAttributesTable.description: A list of target identities which each initiator on the local system may access.

cIscsiIntrAuthAttributesEntry.name: cIscsiIntrAuthAttributesEntry
cIscsiIntrAuthAttributesEntry.description: An entry (row) containing management information applicable to a particular initiator node's authorized target identity.

cIscsiIntrAuthIndex.name: cIscsiIntrAuthIndex
cIscsiIntrAuthIndex.description: An arbitrary integer used to uniquely identify a particular initiator node's authorized target identity within an iSCSI instance present on the local system.

cIscsiIntrAuthIdentity.name: cIscsiIntrAuthIdentity
cIscsiIntrAuthIdentity.description: A pointer to the corresponding IPS-AUTH MIB user entry to which this initiator node should attempt to establish an iSCSI session.

cIscsiSessionAttributesTable.name: cIscsiSessionAttributesTable
cIscsiSessionAttributesTable.description: A list of sessions belonging to each iSCSI instance present on the system.

cIscsiSessionAttributesEntry.name: cIscsiSessionAttributesEntry
cIscsiSessionAttributesEntry.description: An entry (row) containing management information applicable to a particular session.

cIscsiSsnIndex.name: cIscsiSsnIndex
cIscsiSsnIndex.description: An arbitrary integer used to uniquely identify a particular session within an iSCSI instance present on the local system.

cIscsiSsnDirection.name: cIscsiSsnDirection
cIscsiSsnDirection.description: Direction of iSCSI session: InboundSession - session is established from an external initiator to a target within this iSCSI instance. OutboundSession - session is established from an initiator within this iSCSI instance to an external target.

cIscsiSsnInitiatorName.name: cIscsiSsnInitiatorName
cIscsiSsnInitiatorName.description: If cIscsiSsnDirection is Inbound, this object is an octet string that will contain the name of the remote initiator. If cIscsiSsnDirection is Outbound, this object will contain a zero-length string.

cIscsiSsnTargetName.name: cIscsiSsnTargetName
cIscsiSsnTargetName.description: If cIscsiSsnDirection is Outbound, this object is an octet string that will contain the name of the remote target. If cIscsiSsnDirection is Inbound, this object will contain a zero-length string.

cIscsiSsnTsih.name: cIscsiSsnTsih
cIscsiSsnTsih.description: The target-defined identification handle for this session.

cIscsiSsnIsid.name: cIscsiSsnIsid
cIscsiSsnIsid.description: The initiator-defined portion of the iSCSI Session ID.

cIscsiSsnInitiatorAlias.name: cIscsiSsnInitiatorAlias
cIscsiSsnInitiatorAlias.description: An octet string that gives the alias communicated by the initiator end of the session during the login phase. If no alias exists, the value is a zero-length string.

cIscsiSsnTargetAlias.name: cIscsiSsnTargetAlias
cIscsiSsnTargetAlias.description: An octet string that gives the alias communicated by the target end of the session during the login phase. If no alias exists, the value is a zero-length string.

cIscsiSsnInitialR2T.name: cIscsiSsnInitialR2T
cIscsiSsnInitialR2T.description: If set to true, indicates that the initiator must wait for an R2T before sending to the target. If set to false, the initiator may send data immediately, within limits set by cIscsiSsnFirstBurstSize and the expected data transfer length of the request. Default is true.

cIscsiSsnBidiInitialR2T.name: cIscsiSsnBidiInitialR2T
cIscsiSsnBidiInitialR2T.description: If set to true, indicates that the initiator must wait for an R2T before sending data to the target within a bi-directional (both read and write) request. If false, the initiator may send unsolicited write data as part of the request.

cIscsiSsnImmediateData.name: cIscsiSsnImmediateData
cIscsiSsnImmediateData.description: Indicates whether the initiator and target have agreed to support immediate data on this session.

cIscsiSsnType.name: cIscsiSsnType
cIscsiSsnType.description: Type of iSCSI session: normalSession - session is a normal iSCSI session discoverySession - session is being used only for discovery.

cIscsiSsnMaxOutstandingR2T.name: cIscsiSsnMaxOutstandingR2T
cIscsiSsnMaxOutstandingR2T.description: The maximum number of outstanding request-to-transmit (R2T)s per task within this session.

cIscsiSsnFirstBurstSize.name: cIscsiSsnFirstBurstSize
cIscsiSsnFirstBurstSize.description: The maximum length supported for unsolicited data sent within this session.

cIscsiSsnMaxBurstSize.name: cIscsiSsnMaxBurstSize
cIscsiSsnMaxBurstSize.description: The maximum number of bytes which can be sent within a single sequence of Data-In or Data-Out PDUs.

cIscsiSsnConnectionNumber.name: cIscsiSsnConnectionNumber
cIscsiSsnConnectionNumber.description: The number of transport protocol connections that currently belong to this session.

cIscsiSsnAuthIdentity.name: cIscsiSsnAuthIdentity
cIscsiSsnAuthIdentity.description: This object contains a row in the IPS-AUTH MIB which identifies the authentication method being used on this session, as communicated during the login phase.

cIscsiSsnDataSequenceInOrder.name: cIscsiSsnDataSequenceInOrder
cIscsiSsnDataSequenceInOrder.description: False indicates that iSCSI data PDU sequences may be transferred in any order. True indicates that data PDU sequences must be transferred using continuously increasing offsets, except during error recovery.

cIscsiSsnDataPduInOrder.name: cIscsiSsnDataPduInOrder
cIscsiSsnDataPduInOrder.description: False indicates that iSCSI data PDUs within sequences may be in any order. True indicates that data PDUs within sequences must be at continuously increasing addresses, with no gaps or overlay between PDUs. Default is true.

cIscsiSsnErrorRecoveryLevel.name: cIscsiSsnErrorRecoveryLevel
cIscsiSsnErrorRecoveryLevel.description: The level of error recovery negotiated between the initiator and the target. Higher numbers represent more detailed recovery schemes.

cIscsiSessionStatsTable.name: cIscsiSessionStatsTable
cIscsiSessionStatsTable.description: A list of general iSCSI traffic counters for each of the sessions present on the system.

cIscsiSessionStatsEntry.name: cIscsiSessionStatsEntry
cIscsiSessionStatsEntry.description: An entry (row) containing general iSCSI traffic counters for a particular session.

cIscsiSsnCmdPdus.name: cIscsiSsnCmdPdus
cIscsiSsnCmdPdus.description: The count of Command PDUs transferred on this session.

cIscsiSsnRspPdus.name: cIscsiSsnRspPdus
cIscsiSsnRspPdus.description: The count of Response PDUs transferred on this session.

cIscsiSsnTxDataOctets.name: cIscsiSsnTxDataOctets
cIscsiSsnTxDataOctets.description: The count of data octets that were transmitted by the local iSCSI node on this session.

cIscsiSsnRxDataOctets.name: cIscsiSsnRxDataOctets
cIscsiSsnRxDataOctets.description: The count of data octets that were received by the local iSCSI node on this session.

cIscsiSessionCxnErrorStatsTable.name: cIscsiSessionCxnErrorStatsTable
cIscsiSessionCxnErrorStatsTable.description: A list of error counters for each of the sessions present on this system.

cIscsiSessionCxnErrorStatsEntry.name: cIscsiSessionCxnErrorStatsEntry
cIscsiSessionCxnErrorStatsEntry.description: An entry (row) containing error counters for a particular session.

cIscsiSsnDigestErrors.name: cIscsiSsnDigestErrors
cIscsiSsnDigestErrors.description: The count of PDUs which were received on the session and contained header or data digest errors.

cIscsiSsnCxnTimeoutErrors.name: cIscsiSsnCxnTimeoutErrors
cIscsiSsnCxnTimeoutErrors.description: The count of connections within this session which have been terminated due to timeout.

cIscsiConnectionAttributesTable.name: cIscsiConnectionAttributesTable
cIscsiConnectionAttributesTable.description: A list of connections belonging to each iSCSI instance present on the system.

cIscsiConnectionAttributesEntry.name: cIscsiConnectionAttributesEntry
cIscsiConnectionAttributesEntry.description: An entry (row) containing management information applicable to a particular connection.

cIscsiCxnIndex.name: cIscsiCxnIndex
cIscsiCxnIndex.description: An arbitrary integer used to uniquely identify a particular connection of a particular session within an iSCSI instance present on the local system.

cIscsiCxnCid.name: cIscsiCxnCid
cIscsiCxnCid.description: The iSCSI Connection ID for this connection.

cIscsiCxnState.name: cIscsiCxnState
cIscsiCxnState.description: The current state of this connection, from an iSCSI negotiation point of view. Here are the states: login - The transport protocol connection has been established, but a valid iSCSI login response with the final bit set has not been sent or received. full - A valid iSCSI login response with the final bit set has been sent or received. logout - A valid iSCSI logout command has been sent or received, but the transport protocol connection has not yet been closed.

cIscsiCxnLocalAddrType.name: cIscsiCxnLocalAddrType
cIscsiCxnLocalAddrType.description: The type of Internet Network Address in cIscsiCxnLocalAddr.

cIscsiCxnLocalAddr.name: cIscsiCxnLocalAddr
cIscsiCxnLocalAddr.description: The local Internet Network Address used by this connection.

cIscsiCxnProtocol.name: cIscsiCxnProtocol
cIscsiCxnProtocol.description: The transport protocol over which this connection is running.

cIscsiCxnLocalPort.name: cIscsiCxnLocalPort
cIscsiCxnLocalPort.description: The local transport protocol port used by this connection.

cIscsiCxnRemoteAddrType.name: cIscsiCxnRemoteAddrType
cIscsiCxnRemoteAddrType.description: The type of Internet Network Address in cIscsiCxnRemoteAddr.

cIscsiCxnRemoteAddr.name: cIscsiCxnRemoteAddr
cIscsiCxnRemoteAddr.description: The remote Internet Network Address used by this connection.

cIscsiCxnRemotePort.name: cIscsiCxnRemotePort
cIscsiCxnRemotePort.description: The remote transport protocol port used by this connection.

cIscsiCxnMaxRecvDataSegLength.name: cIscsiCxnMaxRecvDataSegLength
cIscsiCxnMaxRecvDataSegLength.description: The maximum data payload size supported for command or data PDUs in use within this connection. Note that the size of reported in bytes even though the negotiation is in 512k blocks.

cIscsiCxnHeaderIntegrity.name: cIscsiCxnHeaderIntegrity
cIscsiCxnHeaderIntegrity.description: This object identifies the iSCSI header digest scheme in use within this connection.

cIscsiCxnDataIntegrity.name: cIscsiCxnDataIntegrity
cIscsiCxnDataIntegrity.description: This object identifies the iSCSI data digest scheme in use within this connection.

cIscsiCxnRecvMarker.name: cIscsiCxnRecvMarker
cIscsiCxnRecvMarker.description: This object indicates whether or not this connection is receiving markers in in its incoming data stream.

cIscsiCxnSendMarker.name: cIscsiCxnSendMarker
cIscsiCxnSendMarker.description: This object indicates whether or not this connection is inserting markers in in its outgoing data stream.

cIscsiTgtLoginFailure.name: cIscsiTgtLoginFailure
cIscsiTgtLoginFailure.description: Sent when a login is failed by a target. The implementation of this trap should not send more than 3 notifications of this type in any 10 second time span.

cIscsiIntrLoginFailure.name: cIscsiIntrLoginFailure
cIscsiIntrLoginFailure.description: Sent when a login is failed by a initiator. The implementation of this trap should not send more than 3 notifications of this type in any 10 second time span.

cIscsiInstSessionFailure.name: cIscsiInstSessionFailure
cIscsiInstSessionFailure.description: Sent when an active session is failed by either the initiator or the target. The implementation of this trap should not send more than 3 notifications of this type in any 10 second time span.

cIscsiInstanceAttributesGroup.name: cIscsiInstanceAttributesGroup
cIscsiInstanceAttributesGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information about iSCSI instances.

cIscsiInstanceSsnErrorStatsGroup.name: cIscsiInstanceSsnErrorStatsGroup
cIscsiInstanceSsnErrorStatsGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information about errors that have caused a session failure for an iSCSI instance.

cIscsiPortalAttributesGroup.name: cIscsiPortalAttributesGroup
cIscsiPortalAttributesGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information about the transport protocol endpoints of the local targets.

cIscsiTgtPortalAttributesGroup.name: cIscsiTgtPortalAttributesGroup
cIscsiTgtPortalAttributesGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information about the transport protocol endpoints of the local targets.

cIscsiIntrPortalAttributesGroup.name: cIscsiIntrPortalAttributesGroup
cIscsiIntrPortalAttributesGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information about the Internet Network Addresses of the local initiators.

cIscsiNodeAttributesGroup.name: cIscsiNodeAttributesGroup
cIscsiNodeAttributesGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information about all local targets.

cIscsiTargetAttributesGroup.name: cIscsiTargetAttributesGroup
cIscsiTargetAttributesGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information about all local targets.

cIscsiTargetLoginStatsGroup.name: cIscsiTargetLoginStatsGroup
cIscsiTargetLoginStatsGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information about all login attempts by remote initiators to local targets.

cIscsiTargetLogoutStatsGroup.name: cIscsiTargetLogoutStatsGroup
cIscsiTargetLogoutStatsGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information about all logout events between remote initiators to local targets.

cIscsiInitiatorAttributesGroup.name: cIscsiInitiatorAttributesGroup
cIscsiInitiatorAttributesGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information about all local initiators.

cIscsiInitiatorLoginStatsGroup.name: cIscsiInitiatorLoginStatsGroup
cIscsiInitiatorLoginStatsGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information about all login attempts by local initiators to remote targets.

cIscsiInitiatorLogoutStatsGroup.name: cIscsiInitiatorLogoutStatsGroup
cIscsiInitiatorLogoutStatsGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information about all logout events between local initiators to remote targets.

cIscsiSessionAttributesGroup.name: cIscsiSessionAttributesGroup
cIscsiSessionAttributesGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information applicable to all sessions.

cIscsiSessionStatsGroup.name: cIscsiSessionStatsGroup
cIscsiSessionStatsGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information about message and data traffic for all sessions.

cIscsiSessionCxnErrorStatsGroup.name: cIscsiSessionCxnErrorStatsGroup
cIscsiSessionCxnErrorStatsGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information about connection errors for all sessions.

cIscsiConnectionAttributesGroup.name: cIscsiConnectionAttributesGroup
cIscsiConnectionAttributesGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information about all connections used by all sessions.

cIscsiTgtLgnNotificationsGroup.name: cIscsiTgtLgnNotificationsGroup
cIscsiTgtLgnNotificationsGroup.description: A collection of notifications which indicate a login failure from a remote initiator to a local target.

cIscsiIntrLgnNotificationsGroup.name: cIscsiIntrLgnNotificationsGroup
cIscsiIntrLgnNotificationsGroup.description: A collection of notifications which indicate a login failure from a local initiator to a remote target.

cIscsiSsnFlrNotificationsGroup.name: cIscsiSsnFlrNotificationsGroup
cIscsiSsnFlrNotificationsGroup.description: A collection of notifications which indicate session failures occurring after login.

cIscsiComplianceV1.name: cIscsiComplianceV1
cIscsiComplianceV1.description: Initial version of compliance statement based on initial version of MIB. If an implementation can be both a target and an initiator, all groups are mandatory.
